Install Emacs
sudo apt update
sudo apt install emacs

Launch Emacs
emacs
Exit Emacs:
Press Ctrl + x then Ctrl + c

Menu bar treminal version
emacs -Q -nw
F10

Learn Navigation (Basic Keys)
Action	Key Combination
Move cursor up	Ctrl + p
Move cursor down	Ctrl + n
Move left	Ctrl + b
Move right	Ctrl + f
Page down	Ctrl + v
Page up	Alt + v
Go to line	Alt + g g or M-g g
Save file	Ctrl + x → Ctrl + s
Open file	Ctrl + x → Ctrl + f
Close Emacs	Ctrl + x → Ctrl + c

How to Open a File (like Ctrl+P in VS Code)
In Emacs, press:
C-x C-f
That means:
Ctrl + x, then
Ctrl + f

Close File (Current Buffer)
C-x k
That means:
Ctrl + x
Then k (for kill-buffer)
